radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; 1.2 cm cyst in the left lobe of the liver; other subcentimeter hypodensities in the liver; dilated and fluid-filled appendix with mild surrounding fat stranding; no evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation; normal pancreas, spleen, kidneys, urinary bladder; no free fluid in the pelvis; no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy; no evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
